   printing speed exhibits S-shaped growth. We also derive various
   structural properties of the problem and devise an efficient algorithm
   to obtain near optimal solutions. Finally, our numerical study shows
   that the 3-D printer is, in general, lightly used under realistic
   parameter settings but results in significant cost savings, suggesting
   complementarity between stock and print in cost minimization.
