   reputation, which we define as the stakeholder's belief regarding the
   accuracy of the agency's information. The agency faces then a trade-off
   between eliciting a proper response today and maintaining its reputation
   to elicit responses to future events. We formulate this problem as a
   dynamic Bayesian persuasion game, which we solve in closed form. We find
   that the agency sometimes strategically misrepresents its advance
